result.execSummary:
The defendant Tara L Wawrzyniec was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tara L Wawrzyniec in court with attorney Daniel T. Cveykus. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  
Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of:  Count 2 - GUILTY
 
Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty of Count 2.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
Counts 1, 3 & 4 are dismissed and read-in. 

Atty Constable makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Cveykus makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 

BY THE COURT:
Count 2 - 
9 months jail, Imposed and Stayed
Huber if approved by the jail administration. 
Placed on probation for a period of  18 months:
Pay fine of $50 plus costs, to include the VWS, filing fee and Drug abuse surcharge. 
Submit a DNA sample and pay the surcharge. 
Perform 100 hours community service.  Required to have 50 hours be done for the Portage County Parks Department during the time she is on probation. 
AODA & comply with treatment recommendations.
Do not possess/consume controlled substances without a valid prescription and be taken according to the prescription. 
Do not possess any drug paraphernalia. 
Do not associate with any persons possessing or consuming illegal controlled substances.
Full-time employment or school full time, or a combination of both resulting in full time.
Engage in any other counseling deemed appropriate by her agent. 

Court advises defendant of post conviction and voting rights. 

Atty Cveykus indicates there was $1,310 taken from the defendant's truck. 
Atty Constable states she will look into the issue but does intend to return the money.  
Court notes if there is an issue, a motion is to be filed according to statutes.
